What you need to know:  Mr Deng met with the Kenyan diplomat on Wednesday after clashes between South Sudan’s Toposa and Kenya’s Turkana communities rocked the border.The two pastoral communities routinely cross the border in search of water and pasture for their livestock.In South Sudan, local and state officials in Eastern Equatorial State claimed in several interviews with media last week that a convoy of Kenyan security officers strayed briefly into South Sudan territory.